00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:57,579 --> 00:01:01,124
THE WONDERFOOLS

2
00:01:02,292 --> 00:01:06,921
EPISODE 8
THE GUARDIANS OF HAESEONG CITY PART 2

3
00:01:09,924 --> 00:01:12,051
Kim Pal-ho, our shepherd,

4
00:01:12,552 --> 00:01:14,387
has been martyred.

5
00:01:19,225 --> 00:01:20,935
Shepherd!

6
00:01:22,854 --> 00:01:24,439
What do we do, Eun Chae-ni?

7
00:01:24,939 --> 00:01:26,774
We're all doomed now.

8
00:01:29,277 --> 00:01:33,448
I may be broke and pathetic,
but I'm still a father and a husband.

9
00:01:33,531 --> 00:01:35,116
The head of my family.

10
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:39,579
My dear Cheong is only 14 years old.

11
00:01:40,538 --> 00:01:44,250
Had I known an apocalypse was coming,
I would've bought her that CD player,

12
00:01:44,334 --> 00:01:46,794
even if it meant being
up to my eyeballs in debt.

13
00:01:47,295 --> 00:01:49,297
What are you crying for?

14
00:01:49,797 --> 00:01:51,216
You could've just said that.

15
00:01:51,299 --> 00:01:52,800
Would that change anything?

16
00:01:52,884 --> 00:01:54,636
What could we even do?

17
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:58,389
They're Wunderkinder,
and apparently, we're just defective.

18
00:01:59,098 --> 00:02:00,141
You're right.

19
00:02:00,642 --> 00:02:03,102
Saying it wouldn't change anything.

20
00:02:04,062 --> 00:02:07,148
So tie your shoelaces tight and get ready

21
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:08,483
to run.

22
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:09,442
What…

23
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,835
Stay back!

24
00:02:28,336 --> 00:02:29,379
Stay back!

25
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,381
I'll slice you up!

26
00:02:31,464 --> 00:02:32,757
She'll slice you up!

27
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,175
I'm Lady Trainwreck!

28
00:02:34,259 --> 00:02:36,010
I'm Royal Nightmare!

29
00:02:37,095 --> 00:02:38,221
Stay back!

30
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:41,349
Stop right there! Stay back!

31
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:44,602
Hey, Eun Chae-ni.
Take us somewhere else, anywhere!

32
00:02:45,353 --> 00:02:46,771
I'd love to,

33
00:02:46,854 --> 00:02:50,275
but I ate my last coffee jelly
to save Ro-bin.

34
00:02:53,569 --> 00:02:57,365
I really hoped I'd get a chance
to say goodbye to Moon Mi-hui and Cheong.

35
00:02:57,448 --> 00:02:58,491
Mr. Son.

36
00:02:58,574 --> 00:02:59,993
Forget it. Don't comfort me!

37
00:03:04,831 --> 00:03:06,416
Just my luck, I guess.

38
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:10,378
I worked my ass off
only to get treated like an ass.

39
00:03:10,461 --> 00:03:11,879
The world's screwed up.

40
00:03:11,963 --> 00:03:14,424
Was the financial crisis my fault?

41
00:03:14,507 --> 00:03:16,676
Is it my fault my company restructured?

42
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:18,428
I'm a victim too.

43
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:21,431
Why am I always treated like a loser?

44
00:03:21,514 --> 00:03:22,765
I don't ask for much!

45
00:03:22,849 --> 00:03:24,475
Why am I always--

46
00:03:36,863 --> 00:03:38,740
Finally, some peace and quiet.

47
00:03:38,823 --> 00:03:40,408
It was a bit noisy, wasn't it?

48
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:43,870
He's not such a bad guy
once you get to know him.

49
00:03:44,370 --> 00:03:46,331
He just likes to talk big.

50
00:03:51,336 --> 00:03:57,842
SON GYEONG-HUN
MOON MI-HUI

51
00:04:01,763 --> 00:04:03,473
Chae-ni, you little shit.

52
00:04:03,556 --> 00:04:04,891
Alrighty, then.

53
00:04:04,974 --> 00:04:07,060
Who's going to come at me first?

54
00:04:07,143 --> 00:04:08,478
<i>Hotteok </i>lady?

55
00:04:08,561 --> 00:04:10,271
Or Mr. Heo from the general store?

56
00:04:10,355 --> 00:04:12,398
You're going to get hurt.

57
00:04:12,482 --> 00:04:14,734
I wonder if you'll be all right with that.

58
00:04:14,817 --> 00:04:16,736
One wrong move and you lose a finger.

59
00:04:16,819 --> 00:04:18,529
Then who'd flip the <i>hotteok</i>?

60
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:23,785
Get her.

61
00:04:26,162 --> 00:04:28,081
Hold up. Stay back!

62
00:04:28,164 --> 00:04:29,415
Don't you dare touch me!

63
00:04:29,499 --> 00:04:30,917
There are too damn many!

64
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,210
You'll get hurt!

65
00:04:32,293 --> 00:04:33,669
Let go, damn it!

66
00:04:33,753 --> 00:04:35,546
I told you not to. Why are you--

67
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:38,841
What do you want with me?

68
00:04:50,353 --> 00:04:51,521
Outsiders!

69
00:04:51,604 --> 00:04:53,231
Let's protect our temple!

70
00:04:53,314 --> 00:04:54,649
Charge!

71
00:05:24,929 --> 00:05:26,264
What the… What was that?

72
00:05:26,347 --> 00:05:28,224
Everyone, freeze!

73
00:05:29,183 --> 00:05:31,644
Get away from my granddaughter!

74
00:05:32,645 --> 00:05:33,479
Grandma?

75
00:05:35,231 --> 00:05:36,107
Eunie!

76
00:05:37,108 --> 00:05:38,151
Grandma!

77
00:05:38,234 --> 00:05:39,152
Take this.

78
00:05:39,652 --> 00:05:40,486
Are you okay?

79
00:05:48,536 --> 00:05:51,789
Look at you.
Did you crawl out of a dumpster?

80
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,835
Grandma, look at yourself first.

81
00:05:55,918 --> 00:05:58,254
Did you not sleep at all last night?

82
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:01,340
Look at the bags under your eyes.
You'll collapse at this rate!

83
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:05,178
The owner of Hearty House?

84
00:06:07,346 --> 00:06:08,639
What brings

85
00:06:09,932 --> 00:06:11,058
you here?

86
00:06:40,588 --> 00:06:41,589
There you are.

87
00:06:42,798 --> 00:06:44,884
I thought you would have gone
to see your mom.

88
00:06:47,136 --> 00:06:48,137
Why us?

89
00:06:49,972 --> 00:06:52,517
I'm just curious why you did
those awful things to us.

90
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,936
There's no particular reason.

91
00:06:55,811 --> 00:06:57,188
All of this started

92
00:06:57,271 --> 00:07:02,652
with humanity's petty desire
to live a long life.

93
00:07:04,153 --> 00:07:05,780
That's how the world works.

94
00:07:08,866 --> 00:07:11,118
Things that may look grand on the outside

95
00:07:11,202 --> 00:07:12,245
often come from

96
00:07:12,954 --> 00:07:16,040
petty greed, petty envy,

97
00:07:16,624 --> 00:07:19,168
and the most trivial of discoveries.

98
00:07:20,628 --> 00:07:24,131
We needed children
to experiment on back then,

99
00:07:24,215 --> 00:07:26,467
and you just happened to be one of them.

100
00:07:27,051 --> 00:07:27,969
So,

101
00:07:28,553 --> 00:07:30,930
don't seek reason or meaning.

102
00:07:31,764 --> 00:07:33,182
There is none.

103
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:37,728
Life merely exists

104
00:07:38,229 --> 00:07:41,774
upon banal coincidences and petty reasons

105
00:07:41,857 --> 00:07:43,401
until we eventually perish.

106
00:07:44,944 --> 00:07:46,028
Petty?

107
00:07:48,698 --> 00:07:50,658
I guess human lives are trivial to you.

108
00:07:50,741 --> 00:07:53,661
Out of the 72 children,

109
00:07:54,328 --> 00:07:55,913
50% of them manifested,

110
00:07:55,997 --> 00:07:59,709
and half of those who manifested
gained abilities.

111
00:08:00,209 --> 00:08:04,171
One of them was the child
with the Heart of Eternity.

112
00:08:04,714 --> 00:08:08,050
That child was the only
meaningful end product.

113
00:08:12,722 --> 00:08:14,640
So I thought

114
00:08:15,641 --> 00:08:18,936
if more people manifested,

115
00:08:19,687 --> 00:08:22,481
then wouldn't the number
of eternal hearts also increase

116
00:08:23,149 --> 00:08:24,483
at a similar probability?

117
00:08:26,193 --> 00:08:27,778
Enough with the riddles.

118
00:08:46,088 --> 00:08:46,964
<i>Are you saying</i>

119
00:08:47,632 --> 00:08:49,550
you'll unleash that drug on Haeseong?

120
00:08:49,634 --> 00:08:52,428
God sometimes brings destruction and chaos

121
00:08:52,511 --> 00:08:54,221
to create a new order.

122
00:08:54,805 --> 00:08:55,640
Are you

123
00:08:56,724 --> 00:08:57,600
actually insane?

124
00:08:59,477 --> 00:09:01,562
What about the children who died?

125
00:09:02,063 --> 00:09:03,773
Among the children experimented on,

126
00:09:04,398 --> 00:09:06,484
half died without ever manifesting.

127
00:09:08,194 --> 00:09:09,695
<i>And of those who manifested,</i>

128
00:09:10,738 --> 00:09:13,115
<i>some died from the physical mutations.</i>

129
00:09:14,116 --> 00:09:17,078
Far more children died
than the few who survived.

130
00:09:21,999 --> 00:09:25,169
For a single coincidence
that may or may not recur,

131
00:09:26,671 --> 00:09:28,673
you're going to kill
all those people again?

132
00:09:28,756 --> 00:09:32,677
It's not the dead children
who change history.

133
00:09:33,302 --> 00:09:34,929
It's you, the survivors.

134
00:09:37,932 --> 00:09:39,266
You actual son of a bitch.

135
00:09:44,730 --> 00:09:46,774
Bring me the Child of Eternity again.

136
00:09:47,358 --> 00:09:52,154
Let us create a new order
in a new world together.

137
00:09:54,615 --> 00:09:56,075
Ko Eun-san.

138
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:59,412
You will become a new breed of humans.

139
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,669
On my way here, I wondered…

140
00:10:09,463 --> 00:10:10,381
if I…

141
00:10:14,427 --> 00:10:16,011
could kill you.

142
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:46,125
A pity.

143
00:10:46,834 --> 00:10:48,878
I was quite fond of you.

144
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,424
Father.

145
00:11:54,777 --> 00:11:55,986
Father!

146
00:12:17,466 --> 00:12:18,509
Master.

147
00:12:20,135 --> 00:12:21,136
Grandma.

148
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:23,389
Handle things here.

149
00:12:23,472 --> 00:12:25,349
What about you?

150
00:12:26,058 --> 00:12:27,852
I don't know if it'll work,

151
00:12:28,435 --> 00:12:30,020
but I really need it to.

152
00:12:30,729 --> 00:12:31,939
Please, let's go.

153
00:12:32,565 --> 00:12:33,816
To Master.

154
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,401
Please!

155
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,918
Hot!

156
00:12:53,002 --> 00:12:54,753
What the… Fire!

157
00:12:56,672 --> 00:12:59,258
Master!

158
00:13:04,054 --> 00:13:04,889
Master?

159
00:13:07,725 --> 00:13:09,727
Oh dear, this isn't the right face.

160
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:11,186
It's not the right face.

161
00:13:14,148 --> 00:13:17,109
This isn't the face I'm looking for.
I can't save you.

162
00:13:18,444 --> 00:13:19,361
Master!

163
00:13:22,156 --> 00:13:23,198
Help me.

164
00:13:23,282 --> 00:13:25,993
Master's face doesn't look like this.

165
00:13:26,076 --> 00:13:26,994
I'm sorry.

166
00:13:30,873 --> 00:13:32,207
Damn it.

167
00:13:36,462 --> 00:13:38,130
Chae-ni, my God--

168
00:13:46,513 --> 00:13:47,514
Call 119!

169
00:13:50,684 --> 00:13:52,895
Answer me! Damn, that's hot!

170
00:13:52,978 --> 00:13:54,229
Master!

171
00:14:03,781 --> 00:14:07,159
Eunie, that's enough.

172
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:10,371
We just called 119.

173
00:14:12,039 --> 00:14:13,374
Grandma, he's not there.

174
00:14:16,377 --> 00:14:17,878
Master.

175
00:14:20,464 --> 00:14:21,966
I can't find him.

176
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:14,309
Father.

177
00:15:14,393 --> 00:15:16,145
Father, it's me. Father?

178
00:16:24,713 --> 00:16:25,923
Hey, Ju-ran.

179
00:16:26,632 --> 00:16:28,717
We'll be in downtown Haeseong
in 15 minutes.

180
00:16:30,511 --> 00:16:31,386
All right.

181
00:16:31,887 --> 00:16:33,806
Don't let anything go wrong.

182
00:16:34,306 --> 00:16:35,724
No matter what happens…

183
00:16:38,477 --> 00:16:39,561
stick to the plan.

184
00:16:41,063 --> 00:16:42,022
Ju-ran.

185
00:16:43,941 --> 00:16:45,234
Everything's okay, right?

186
00:16:50,948 --> 00:16:51,949
Yeah.

187
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,118
Everything's fine.

188
00:16:54,701 --> 00:16:56,245
When's Pal-ho joining us?

189
00:16:58,914 --> 00:17:00,791
<i>Pal-ho can't make it, Ho-ran.</i>

190
00:17:02,417 --> 00:17:04,044
I'll send someone else instead.

191
00:17:05,754 --> 00:17:06,588
Who?

192
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:02,144
I'm sorry about back then.

193
00:18:02,895 --> 00:18:03,979
Sir!

194
00:18:04,062 --> 00:18:05,522
Please open this door.

195
00:18:07,024 --> 00:18:09,359
Sir, please!

196
00:18:09,443 --> 00:18:10,652
Sir!

197
00:18:10,736 --> 00:18:12,196
<i>Sir!</i>

198
00:18:13,655 --> 00:18:17,242
The debt I owe you from back then,
let me settle it now.

199
00:18:19,286 --> 00:18:21,038
The door is wide open now,

200
00:18:21,538 --> 00:18:25,042
so go and live your life to the fullest.

201
00:18:25,918 --> 00:18:27,044
Okay?

202
00:18:40,891 --> 00:18:42,142
<i>Number 3972.</i>

203
00:18:43,268 --> 00:18:44,353
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

204
00:18:46,355 --> 00:18:47,564
<i>Number 3972.</i>

205
00:18:56,156 --> 00:18:57,908
Yeah, okay. Bye.

206
00:18:57,991 --> 00:18:58,867
Grandma.

207
00:19:01,119 --> 00:19:03,038
One of the believers says

208
00:19:03,121 --> 00:19:06,416
two container trucks headed downtown
early this morning.

209
00:19:07,376 --> 00:19:08,794
What was loaded in them?

210
00:19:08,877 --> 00:19:11,046
I don't know the details.

211
00:19:11,713 --> 00:19:13,882
I just saw them leave early this morning.

212
00:19:17,469 --> 00:19:18,845
They're loaded with a drug.

213
00:19:20,138 --> 00:19:22,057
Royal Nightmare said he saw it.

214
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:24,226
They're planning to spray it
all over Haeseong.

215
00:19:27,145 --> 00:19:28,146
Should we report it?

216
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:29,481
There's no point.

217
00:19:30,482 --> 00:19:32,150
That bastard, Byeong-jin,

218
00:19:32,234 --> 00:19:34,861
is already under the influence
of the Church.

219
00:19:36,154 --> 00:19:37,906
I'd better meet the mayor first.

220
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,700
That won't be necessary.

221
00:19:43,161 --> 00:19:44,371
Holy Mother.

222
00:19:44,913 --> 00:19:46,790
Holy Mother.

223
00:19:47,291 --> 00:19:48,875
Holy Mother.

224
00:20:02,889 --> 00:20:04,433
Are you another one of those kids?

225
00:20:12,774 --> 00:20:14,318
You look badly hurt.

226
00:20:14,401 --> 00:20:15,402
Don't move.

227
00:20:17,863 --> 00:20:21,366
Hey, Mr. Gu, are you insane?
What do you think you're doing?

228
00:20:24,202 --> 00:20:26,913
Stop it.
Don't mess with Grandma or Mr. Gu.

229
00:20:26,997 --> 00:20:30,917
If you have something to say,
say it to me. Don't mess with my family!

230
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:35,422
I already lost my brother

231
00:20:36,381 --> 00:20:37,466
and my father.

232
00:20:40,969 --> 00:20:42,679
Now it's your turn.

233
00:20:42,763 --> 00:20:43,680
No!

234
00:20:50,312 --> 00:20:52,064
She'll be back.

235
00:20:53,357 --> 00:20:54,816
The moment she shows up,

236
00:20:56,026 --> 00:20:56,860
shoot her.

237
00:21:10,582 --> 00:21:13,627
If you want to live, move!

238
00:21:20,634 --> 00:21:21,968
I said move!

239
00:21:27,641 --> 00:21:29,351
Chae-ni, you're so freaking cool.

240
00:21:29,851 --> 00:21:31,353
Here goes!

241
00:21:35,857 --> 00:21:36,858
Here I go.

242
00:21:38,693 --> 00:21:40,320
Yeah!

243
00:21:40,946 --> 00:21:43,323
Eun Chae-ni, coming through!

244
00:21:45,742 --> 00:21:47,119
Now! Get her out!

245
00:22:00,090 --> 00:22:01,299
So refreshing.

246
00:22:33,623 --> 00:22:34,499
Cheong.

247
00:22:39,629 --> 00:22:40,464
What about Dad?

248
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,758
Don't worry about it, honey.

249
00:22:45,552 --> 00:22:49,890
How dare he stay out all night.
At this point, he's asking for a divorce.

250
00:22:51,057 --> 00:22:52,142
You're divorcing?

251
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:58,148
Don't worry about anything
and just focus on the rehearsal, okay?

252
00:22:58,773 --> 00:22:59,900
Stand up straight!

253
00:23:00,692 --> 00:23:02,194
Honey, say cheese!

254
00:23:07,616 --> 00:23:10,660
Please just gather around for a moment.
Thank you, everyone.

255
00:23:10,744 --> 00:23:11,870
Thank you all so much.

256
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:15,123
I'm so grateful to see you
working so hard. Hello, Mayor.

257
00:23:17,542 --> 00:23:22,547
Tonight's parade will start
exactly at eleven o'clock as planned.

258
00:23:22,631 --> 00:23:25,467
As we rehearsed,
the order will be as follows.

259
00:23:25,550 --> 00:23:29,429
First, the flag bearers,
then the marching band will follow.

260
00:23:29,513 --> 00:23:31,640
Then, the Changwon Samulnori Troupe will--

261
00:23:31,723 --> 00:23:33,642
Everybody, stop!

262
00:23:34,226 --> 00:23:35,519
Everyone!

263
00:23:35,602 --> 00:23:37,646
-Who, why? What is it?
-Everyone, stop!

264
00:23:37,729 --> 00:23:40,815
Stop what you're doing, all of you,
and get out of here!

265
00:23:40,899 --> 00:23:42,192
Everybody stop!

266
00:23:43,193 --> 00:23:45,111
Stop what you're doing
and get out of here.

267
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:46,780
You can't stay here.

268
00:23:46,863 --> 00:23:48,740
-Why not?
-You can't stay here!

269
00:23:49,407 --> 00:23:51,117
What's going on, huh?

270
00:23:51,201 --> 00:23:54,371
Honey! What are you doing over there?

271
00:23:55,580 --> 00:23:56,456
Honey!

272
00:23:57,958 --> 00:23:58,833
Honey!

273
00:23:58,917 --> 00:24:00,627
Honey!

274
00:24:01,711 --> 00:24:02,879
You're here too?

275
00:24:04,047 --> 00:24:05,924
Cheong!

276
00:24:06,007 --> 00:24:07,384
My darling Cheong as well?

277
00:24:07,467 --> 00:24:08,635
Cheong!

278
00:24:09,344 --> 00:24:10,595
You can't stay here.

279
00:24:10,679 --> 00:24:13,723
Honey, come with me.
We have to go. This isn't a drill!

280
00:24:13,807 --> 00:24:18,061
Why on earth are you doing this
in front of all these people?

281
00:24:18,144 --> 00:24:21,273
That's how urgent and dangerous
the situation is. Let's go, now!

282
00:24:21,856 --> 00:24:24,818
-Let's go!
-Go where?

283
00:24:24,901 --> 00:24:26,903
Do you know how long
she's waited for today?

284
00:24:26,987 --> 00:24:29,823
She was chosen to represent her grade,
not just her class.

285
00:24:29,906 --> 00:24:31,408
What would you know?

286
00:24:31,491 --> 00:24:34,536
Being the damn grade representative
doesn't matter right now!

287
00:24:35,870 --> 00:24:37,664
The apocalypse is coming!

288
00:24:37,747 --> 00:24:38,748
Seriously?

289
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,668
Screw the new millennium!

290
00:24:42,294 --> 00:24:44,671
Everything will disappear in an instant!

291
00:24:46,047 --> 00:24:48,550
If you keep embarrassing me like this,

292
00:24:49,050 --> 00:24:50,468
you'll be the one to disappear.

293
00:24:51,886 --> 00:24:53,555
From Cheong's life and mine.

294
00:24:54,055 --> 00:24:54,889
Forever.

295
00:24:57,392 --> 00:24:58,977
-Honey.
-Stop embarrassing me!

296
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:00,562
Honey, you have to listen to me!

297
00:25:02,606 --> 00:25:03,732
-Come on.
-Mr. Yang.

298
00:25:04,482 --> 00:25:05,400
Listen to me!

299
00:25:06,318 --> 00:25:08,570
Please tell everyone to evacuate.

300
00:25:08,653 --> 00:25:10,780
The guys at the Church
of Eternal Salvation.

301
00:25:10,864 --> 00:25:13,241
Do you know what they're trying to do
to Haeseong?

302
00:25:13,325 --> 00:25:14,826
I do.

303
00:25:16,328 --> 00:25:17,579
You do?

304
00:25:17,662 --> 00:25:20,540
They donated a whopping 100 million won
for this festival.

305
00:25:20,624 --> 00:25:23,001
Thanks to them,
we were able to make a giant version

306
00:25:23,084 --> 00:25:24,586
of our city mascot, Yang-soon,

307
00:25:24,669 --> 00:25:27,380
and even have a fireworks show tonight.

308
00:25:27,464 --> 00:25:29,633
It's all just a cover!

309
00:25:29,716 --> 00:25:32,135
You mustn't fall for it!

310
00:25:32,636 --> 00:25:35,555
Please just listen to me!

311
00:25:36,181 --> 00:25:37,390
Damn it, that hurts!

312
00:25:37,474 --> 00:25:41,394
First you said that a pigeon
blinked its eyes sideways like this,

313
00:25:41,478 --> 00:25:43,396
then a carp this big winked at you.

314
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:45,649
That it was because of phenol
and dumped waste,

315
00:25:45,732 --> 00:25:48,193
and now you're blaming it on the Church?

316
00:25:48,276 --> 00:25:49,986
-That's right!
-Fine, okay.

317
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:53,031
For matters like these,
go ahead and file a complaint,

318
00:25:53,114 --> 00:25:54,574
but please hold off for today.

319
00:25:54,658 --> 00:25:56,409
It's a festival, after all.

320
00:25:56,493 --> 00:26:00,747
The anticipated new millennium is upon us.
You can't rain on our parade like this.

321
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:03,833
Your daughter is even a flag bearer.

322
00:26:03,917 --> 00:26:04,918
Cut it out.

323
00:26:05,001 --> 00:26:06,795
Just call the police.

324
00:26:06,878 --> 00:26:09,756
Royal Nightmare can't stand to see
other people happy.

325
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:11,299
-All right.
-Always grumbling.

326
00:26:11,383 --> 00:26:13,843
-Come on now.
-He's always complaining.

327
00:26:14,344 --> 00:26:17,514
I'll take care of it. I will.

328
00:26:17,597 --> 00:26:18,431
Cheong.

329
00:26:18,932 --> 00:26:21,768
Goodness, isn't he embarrassed
in front of his daughter?

330
00:26:21,851 --> 00:26:23,812
-Exactly!
-That's a bit harsh.

331
00:26:23,895 --> 00:26:25,689
His daughter is here listening, so…

332
00:26:38,618 --> 00:26:39,536
Mr. Son?

333
00:26:44,874 --> 00:26:45,709
Chae-ni!

334
00:26:59,139 --> 00:27:02,267
Master is gone,
and Grandma isn't here either.

335
00:27:03,601 --> 00:27:04,811
What do we do now?

336
00:27:04,894 --> 00:27:06,229
What do you mean?

337
00:27:07,772 --> 00:27:10,942
We'll face the apocalypse
like this, together.

338
00:27:23,037 --> 00:27:26,875
Should we just run away by ourselves?
What a load of nonsense!

339
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:29,919
How could I leave Moon Mi-hui
and Cheong behind? Are you mad?

340
00:27:36,342 --> 00:27:38,261
Chae-ni, what are we going to do?

341
00:27:38,845 --> 00:27:40,054
Come to think of it,

342
00:27:40,555 --> 00:27:43,141
I never got to take a picture with Master.

343
00:27:43,224 --> 00:27:44,350
Excuse me?

344
00:27:45,185 --> 00:27:48,062
How can you talk about pictures
at a time like this?

345
00:27:48,563 --> 00:27:50,315
The apocalypse is coming for Haeseong!

346
00:27:50,398 --> 00:27:53,568
You, me, everyone. We'll all be wiped out.

347
00:27:54,569 --> 00:27:56,571
We're the only ones who know that,

348
00:27:56,654 --> 00:27:59,157
but there's nothing
we can do about it. Why?

349
00:27:59,657 --> 00:28:02,660
Because no one believes us. Why?

350
00:28:05,246 --> 00:28:07,582
Because we're nobodies.

351
00:28:13,004 --> 00:28:14,214
REWARD GRAPES

352
00:28:14,297 --> 00:28:15,590
GREAT JOB

353
00:28:25,517 --> 00:28:27,060
First, let's stop the trucks.

354
00:28:27,143 --> 00:28:28,269
What trucks?

355
00:28:29,062 --> 00:28:31,564
The trucks with the drug
are somewhere in Haeseong.

356
00:28:31,648 --> 00:28:33,608
They're going to blow it up somewhere.

357
00:28:33,691 --> 00:28:35,318
Where exactly?

358
00:28:35,401 --> 00:28:36,820
Where else?

359
00:28:36,903 --> 00:28:40,031
The place where the most people
are gathered in Haeseong right now.

360
00:28:42,534 --> 00:28:44,035
Where do you think?

361
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:46,871
-Where?
-Where?

362
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:51,042
-Sorry, excuse us.
-Move.

363
00:28:51,125 --> 00:28:52,460
-Why's it so crowded?
-Please.

364
00:28:52,544 --> 00:28:54,712
-Move.
-The mascot of Haeseong!

365
00:28:54,796 --> 00:28:56,005
-Too crowded!
-Yang-soon.

366
00:28:56,089 --> 00:28:57,382
Buy a Yang-soon T-shirt!

367
00:28:57,465 --> 00:28:58,967
Look at Yang-soon!

368
00:28:59,050 --> 00:29:00,343
Hey, isn't that Chae-ni?

369
00:29:02,512 --> 00:29:05,765
Have you seen any
Church of Eternal Salvation trucks?

370
00:29:06,599 --> 00:29:07,475
No, we haven't.

371
00:29:09,185 --> 00:29:11,229
Leave Haeseong right now, okay?

372
00:29:11,312 --> 00:29:12,438
Or you'll all die!

373
00:29:12,522 --> 00:29:13,648
You'll die!

374
00:29:13,731 --> 00:29:15,275
-Leave Haeseong.
-What did she say?

375
00:29:15,358 --> 00:29:16,276
-Die?
-Leave!

376
00:29:16,359 --> 00:29:17,902
What is she talking about?

377
00:29:17,986 --> 00:29:19,320
This tastes awful.

378
00:29:19,904 --> 00:29:21,948
What kind of truck is this? What kind?

379
00:29:22,448 --> 00:29:24,492
Are you from the Church? What's in here?

380
00:29:24,576 --> 00:29:26,911
-What is this woman doing?
-Guess not. Pass.

381
00:29:26,995 --> 00:29:28,746
-Welcome.
-Okay!

382
00:29:35,503 --> 00:29:36,796
Who are you?

383
00:29:39,048 --> 00:29:40,008
What are you doing?

384
00:29:40,091 --> 00:29:42,176
You're clueless!

385
00:29:42,260 --> 00:29:43,303
What's he saying?

386
00:29:43,386 --> 00:29:46,681
I did touch the goods,
but there's something really important--

387
00:29:46,764 --> 00:29:47,932
Hey, shut it.

388
00:29:48,016 --> 00:29:50,643
By the looks of you,
you're a repeat offender.

389
00:29:50,727 --> 00:29:53,062
-Why I oughta…
-Don't judge me based on my looks--

390
00:29:53,146 --> 00:29:54,022
Ro-bin!

391
00:29:54,105 --> 00:29:55,481
You don't even have a clue!

392
00:29:55,565 --> 00:29:56,816
What the heck, man!

393
00:29:57,442 --> 00:29:59,444
You got your ass kicked already?

394
00:30:00,653 --> 00:30:02,363
This is so exhausting.

395
00:30:04,198 --> 00:30:07,535
Why are we even going to such lengths?

396
00:30:07,619 --> 00:30:09,120
We have to save the people.

397
00:30:09,203 --> 00:30:12,290
Why are we responsible for the lives
of people we don't even know?

398
00:30:13,374 --> 00:30:14,542
True.

399
00:30:15,043 --> 00:30:17,170
We don't have to save people
we don't know.

400
00:30:17,253 --> 00:30:18,338
Right?

401
00:30:19,422 --> 00:30:20,965
But we know everyone here.

402
00:30:22,717 --> 00:30:23,551
Look.

403
00:30:28,097 --> 00:30:29,849
We really do know everyone here.

404
00:30:29,933 --> 00:30:32,477
Let's help the less fortunate.

405
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:33,436
So what do we do?

406
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:35,396
-Hello.
-Wishing you good health.

407
00:30:35,897 --> 00:30:36,773
Yes, hello.

408
00:30:36,856 --> 00:30:39,359
-Long time, no see.
-Yes, take care.

409
00:30:39,442 --> 00:30:43,863
We don't even have friends,
so how do we know so many people?

410
00:30:44,822 --> 00:30:47,909
Stop grumbling.
Let's hurry up and find them.

411
00:30:47,992 --> 00:30:49,577
We don't have time!

412
00:30:49,661 --> 00:30:50,912
Okay? Just go!

413
00:30:54,791 --> 00:30:57,126
-They're here!
-I think they're here!

414
00:30:57,210 --> 00:30:58,628
-The parade!
-You're right.

415
00:30:58,711 --> 00:31:00,254
What is it?

416
00:31:00,338 --> 00:31:02,006
-What is that?
-What?

417
00:31:02,090 --> 00:31:03,216
Where are they?

418
00:31:04,676 --> 00:31:05,635
Cheong.

419
00:31:06,719 --> 00:31:07,553
Cheong.

420
00:31:07,637 --> 00:31:11,224
ADIEU 1999, TOWARD THE YEAR 2000
A NEW MILLENNIUM, A NEW HOPE

421
00:31:23,277 --> 00:31:25,154
MILLENNIUM GRAND FESTIVAL
HAESEONG 2000

422
00:31:45,800 --> 00:31:48,636
One, two. One, two, three, four.

423
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,972
One, two, three.

424
00:31:52,056 --> 00:31:54,100
-Chae-ni, wait up.
-Hurry!

425
00:31:54,183 --> 00:31:55,309
I said wait.

426
00:31:56,644 --> 00:31:58,271
-One second.
-Still so unfit.

427
00:31:58,354 --> 00:31:59,939
Why? What is it?

428
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:07,405
Master?

429
00:32:09,741 --> 00:32:11,242
You escaped?

430
00:32:11,743 --> 00:32:12,994
When?

431
00:32:13,077 --> 00:32:14,662
How?

432
00:32:14,746 --> 00:32:17,123
I'm so glad you're safe.
I knew you would be, Master.

433
00:32:17,206 --> 00:32:19,542
I knew you would be, Master.

434
00:32:28,301 --> 00:32:30,344
-Master.
-Master?

435
00:32:30,428 --> 00:32:32,013
What'd you do that for?

436
00:32:57,872 --> 00:33:01,209
I thought words were the only thing
that could hurt me.

437
00:33:03,002 --> 00:33:06,380
I'm really upset right now, Master.
You know that?

438
00:33:12,512 --> 00:33:14,180
There is nothing…

439
00:33:16,349 --> 00:33:17,892
you can do.

440
00:33:42,250 --> 00:33:44,502
There she is. There's my daughter.

441
00:33:44,585 --> 00:33:47,255
Cheong!

442
00:33:49,006 --> 00:33:49,841
Cheong!

443
00:34:08,067 --> 00:34:09,610
My daughter's awesome.

444
00:34:11,362 --> 00:34:12,613
So freaking fabulous.

445
00:34:22,331 --> 00:34:23,708
Don't worry, Cheong.

446
00:34:26,752 --> 00:34:30,590
I'll do whatever it takes to stop them.

447
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:33,426
-Stop what?
-You scared me! Honey.

448
00:34:33,509 --> 00:34:35,928
Why don't you stop blocking the road?

449
00:34:36,012 --> 00:34:38,556
We need to reserve a good spot
to see the fireworks.

450
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:40,600
-We can't go to see the fireworks.
-Move.

451
00:34:40,683 --> 00:34:43,019
-Honey, please.
-I need to claim a good spot.

452
00:34:45,271 --> 00:34:46,689
The fireworks.

453
00:34:47,481 --> 00:34:50,359
<i>Do you know what the Church</i>
<i>is trying to do to Haeseong?</i>

454
00:34:50,443 --> 00:34:51,277
<i>I do.</i>

455
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:54,280
They donated a whopping 100 million won
for this festival.

456
00:34:54,363 --> 00:34:56,699
Thanks to them,
we were able to make a giant version

457
00:34:56,782 --> 00:34:58,284
of our city mascot, Yang-soon,

458
00:34:58,367 --> 00:35:00,786
and even have a fireworks show tonight.

459
00:35:02,705 --> 00:35:04,582
That's it. The fireworks.

460
00:35:06,500 --> 00:35:08,211
Up in the sky, in one go.

461
00:35:12,882 --> 00:35:13,716
Boom!

462
00:35:24,435 --> 00:35:25,561
Cheong!

463
00:35:26,187 --> 00:35:29,482
Honey!

464
00:35:39,283 --> 00:35:41,035
Honey!

465
00:35:41,118 --> 00:35:42,495
-Are you okay?
-Honey!

466
00:35:42,578 --> 00:35:44,872
-Are you okay? Cheong!
-Where's Cheong?

467
00:35:45,373 --> 00:35:47,458
Don't come here. Run!

468
00:35:47,541 --> 00:35:48,709
Get behind me.

469
00:35:50,294 --> 00:35:51,837
Are you okay?

470
00:35:51,921 --> 00:35:53,965
Are you okay? Move!

471
00:35:54,757 --> 00:35:56,634
Come this way.

472
00:36:03,641 --> 00:36:06,394
Get inside. It's okay.

473
00:36:10,231 --> 00:36:11,107
What the…

474
00:36:12,733 --> 00:36:16,570
It's already started? I thought she was
sending someone else instead of Pal-ho.

475
00:36:31,210 --> 00:36:32,378
Hey, Master.

476
00:36:32,878 --> 00:36:34,463
Are you mad at us or something?

477
00:36:35,131 --> 00:36:36,632
Let's talk it out.

478
00:36:37,216 --> 00:36:40,886
It's her. The one with the gloomy face
who brainwashes and uses people.

479
00:36:40,970 --> 00:36:43,973
She even made Mr. Gu
point a gun at Grandma earlier.

480
00:36:44,056 --> 00:36:45,099
Really?

481
00:37:02,491 --> 00:37:03,701
Chae-ni!

482
00:37:12,585 --> 00:37:13,419
Master.

483
00:37:46,786 --> 00:37:47,912
Master!

484
00:37:47,995 --> 00:37:49,080
Chae-ni!

485
00:37:56,754 --> 00:37:57,963
Chae-ni.

486
00:38:06,389 --> 00:38:08,140
Snap out of it, Choi Un-jeong!

487
00:38:21,654 --> 00:38:22,571
It's <i>Lee </i>Un-jeong.

488
00:38:25,741 --> 00:38:29,120
I thought
you were really going to kill me.

489
00:38:29,203 --> 00:38:31,956
How could you choke me so hard?

490
00:39:04,155 --> 00:39:06,115
-Cars flying around…
-Stop talking and…

491
00:39:06,657 --> 00:39:08,701
What the…

492
00:39:09,285 --> 00:39:10,453
Why won't you listen?

493
00:39:10,536 --> 00:39:11,745
What's with them?

494
00:39:11,829 --> 00:39:13,205
Why are they acting like that?

495
00:39:13,706 --> 00:39:15,416
Sir, where are you going?

496
00:39:17,835 --> 00:39:21,088
Don't worry. I'm sure
our shepherd left some instructions.

497
00:39:21,172 --> 00:39:22,089
-Really?
-He did?

498
00:39:22,173 --> 00:39:24,216
Why? What's up there?

499
00:39:24,300 --> 00:39:25,342
Where are you going?

500
00:39:25,426 --> 00:39:27,553
No! You can't go there.

501
00:39:27,636 --> 00:39:29,096
Where do you think you're going?

502
00:39:29,180 --> 00:39:30,806
-Must be that way.
-They're strange.

503
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:32,308
-Should we go too?
-Shut it.

504
00:39:32,391 --> 00:39:33,767
Something's up with them.

505
00:40:03,589 --> 00:40:04,673
Chae-ni!

506
00:40:06,217 --> 00:40:07,301
Master!

507
00:40:33,410 --> 00:40:34,578
You two stay here.

508
00:40:34,662 --> 00:40:36,830
No matter what happens, don't come out.

509
00:40:36,914 --> 00:40:37,748
Am I clear?

510
00:40:37,831 --> 00:40:38,999
Are you insane?

511
00:40:39,750 --> 00:40:41,961
Where do you think you're going,
leaving us here?

512
00:40:42,044 --> 00:40:43,546
You have to protect us!

513
00:40:43,629 --> 00:40:45,881
I have to get out there to protect you.

514
00:40:45,965 --> 00:40:47,925
What could you do out there?

515
00:40:48,425 --> 00:40:50,678
What can you do about a car flying at you?

516
00:40:51,178 --> 00:40:53,389
Think you can stop that
with your smart mouth?

517
00:40:53,472 --> 00:40:54,807
Good point.

518
00:40:55,307 --> 00:40:58,852
But it turns out there is something
I can do with my smart mouth.

519
00:41:02,690 --> 00:41:04,817
If you go out there now,

520
00:41:05,859 --> 00:41:07,069
I really will divorce you.

521
00:41:08,862 --> 00:41:10,698
I'm serious this time.

522
00:41:30,634 --> 00:41:32,303
No, honey!

523
00:42:07,338 --> 00:42:08,589
I love you,

524
00:42:09,381 --> 00:42:10,341
Mi-hui.

525
00:42:10,424 --> 00:42:12,051
You dummy!

526
00:42:23,062 --> 00:42:25,356
Mr. Son Gyeong-hun! What took you so long?

527
00:42:26,023 --> 00:42:29,193
I'll handle the side with more people.
You take that side, Mr. Kang.

528
00:42:29,276 --> 00:42:31,153
Can someone insult me?

529
00:42:31,236 --> 00:42:33,864
Are you going to rely on
someone insulting you forever?

530
00:42:33,947 --> 00:42:37,826
Why don't you try to drum up some strength
on your own, you oversized moron?

531
00:42:39,328 --> 00:42:40,329
They're coming.

532
00:43:04,561 --> 00:43:05,521
Isn't it fascinating?

533
00:43:07,856 --> 00:43:08,982
I'm scared!

534
00:43:24,623 --> 00:43:25,457
Get back!

535
00:43:33,924 --> 00:43:35,217
Hey, stay back!

536
00:43:39,972 --> 00:43:41,056
That wasn't me.

537
00:43:41,140 --> 00:43:42,391
I'm your father!

538
00:43:44,143 --> 00:43:45,811
I'm your mother!

539
00:44:20,637 --> 00:44:21,472
I'm sorry.

540
00:44:27,186 --> 00:44:29,354
No. Don't do it--

541
00:44:37,404 --> 00:44:38,447
Ma'am?

542
00:44:39,323 --> 00:44:40,365
Please insult me.

543
00:44:40,449 --> 00:44:41,366
What?

544
00:44:41,450 --> 00:44:42,576
Hurry.

545
00:44:44,077 --> 00:44:45,370
For crying out loud.

546
00:44:45,454 --> 00:44:48,332
How dare this rootless
good-for-nothing bastard

547
00:44:48,415 --> 00:44:51,001
show up out of nowhere
and act like a bumbling idiot!

548
00:44:51,084 --> 00:44:54,463
Should I pop your eyeballs out
and chew them up like radish kimchi?

549
00:44:54,546 --> 00:44:58,258
Why, I should gouge your eyes out
and suck the ink out of them dry.

550
00:44:58,342 --> 00:44:59,635
Want me to whoop your ass?

551
00:44:59,718 --> 00:45:02,471
You dirty bastard with shit for brains.

552
00:45:02,554 --> 00:45:03,931
Piss off, you rotten bastard!

553
00:45:43,428 --> 00:45:44,680
Bam!

554
00:45:46,557 --> 00:45:48,058
Honk honk!

555
00:45:55,399 --> 00:45:59,403
Anyone who wants to roll around
with me, stick here!

556
00:45:59,486 --> 00:46:01,446
This is so exciting!

557
00:46:02,948 --> 00:46:04,449
This is so much fun!

558
00:46:06,577 --> 00:46:09,079
<i>Let's all go on a walk</i>
<i>Around the neighborhood</i>

559
00:46:09,162 --> 00:46:12,249
<i>Wake up early in the dead of night</i>
<i>Walk around the neighborhood</i>

560
00:46:12,332 --> 00:46:15,085
<i>Yang-soon says hello to us too</i>

561
00:46:15,168 --> 00:46:18,422
<i>We all say hello</i>
<i>As we walk around the neighborhood</i>

562
00:46:22,134 --> 00:46:25,262
I swear, I've never…
You must be completely nuts.

563
00:46:25,345 --> 00:46:28,473
You and your shenanigans!

564
00:46:41,236 --> 00:46:42,195
We're back.

565
00:46:42,696 --> 00:46:43,822
That

566
00:46:44,448 --> 00:46:45,282
worked.

567
00:46:45,365 --> 00:46:46,658
Yeah.

568
00:46:47,159 --> 00:46:48,285
It worked.

569
00:46:48,368 --> 00:46:49,912
-Ouch.
-Mr. Son!

570
00:46:49,995 --> 00:46:51,663
Chae-ni! My goodness.

571
00:46:58,962 --> 00:46:59,796
Cheong.

572
00:47:00,380 --> 00:47:01,840
What did we

573
00:47:02,466 --> 00:47:03,634
just see?

574
00:47:04,468 --> 00:47:07,179
Superheroes?

575
00:47:17,356 --> 00:47:20,317
Is it time to clean up now?
Are you even listening?

576
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:23,153
Did that really just happen?

577
00:47:23,654 --> 00:47:26,406
Or is this a prank show?
I didn't hear anything about it.

578
00:47:26,490 --> 00:47:30,619
That's why he was a special recruit.
For his superpower.

579
00:47:30,702 --> 00:47:33,163
I thought he'd hit his peak.

580
00:47:34,206 --> 00:47:36,416
To think he's even hotter than I thought.

581
00:47:38,043 --> 00:47:38,877
Un-jeong--

582
00:47:52,349 --> 00:47:55,477
I just hit them with this,
and the people over there…

583
00:48:10,450 --> 00:48:11,994
Look!

584
00:48:12,077 --> 00:48:13,370
Run!

585
00:48:13,453 --> 00:48:16,289
-Just run!
-Should we go down here?

586
00:48:23,422 --> 00:48:25,465
This really is endless.

587
00:48:26,633 --> 00:48:28,093
She's brainwashing them.

588
00:48:28,593 --> 00:48:30,637
This won't end unless we find her.

589
00:48:30,721 --> 00:48:32,597
No, we have to stop the fireworks first.

590
00:48:33,598 --> 00:48:37,227
There'll be fireworks at midnight,
and it's likely the drug is inside them.

591
00:48:37,310 --> 00:48:40,355
They'll gather people on the streets
for the countdown

592
00:48:40,439 --> 00:48:43,191
then, at midnight, with a single… boom!

593
00:48:47,195 --> 00:48:49,114
Midnight is less than 30 minutes away.

594
00:48:49,197 --> 00:48:50,115
So what do we do?

595
00:48:50,198 --> 00:48:52,576
Deal with the brainwashing woman first,
or the fireworks?

596
00:48:52,659 --> 00:48:54,536
I'll take care of the fireworks!

597
00:48:54,619 --> 00:48:55,829
Mr. Kang, you go with her.

598
00:48:55,912 --> 00:48:58,707
Mr. Son, you can find
the brainwashing woman.

599
00:48:58,790 --> 00:49:00,125
She must be nearby.

600
00:49:06,840 --> 00:49:07,799
Hurry!

601
00:49:13,472 --> 00:49:15,098
I am Spider-Man.

602
00:49:16,016 --> 00:49:17,392
I am a virgin ghost.

603
00:49:17,476 --> 00:49:19,394
I am Frankenstein.

604
00:49:19,895 --> 00:49:21,313
I'm the Hong Kong Granny Ghost.

605
00:49:22,147 --> 00:49:23,899
Oh my!

606
00:49:24,983 --> 00:49:26,151
Oh my goodness!

607
00:49:36,161 --> 00:49:38,163
<i>Hurry, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.</i>

608
00:49:53,678 --> 00:49:54,513
There it is.

609
00:49:54,596 --> 00:49:56,348
-Chae-ni.
-We're in the right place.

610
00:49:56,431 --> 00:49:57,557
Damn it.

611
00:50:05,690 --> 00:50:07,025
Damn.

612
00:50:32,592 --> 00:50:36,054
In these things here? Are these the drugs?
Where are the fireworks?

613
00:50:36,138 --> 00:50:37,055
I'll check these.

614
00:50:39,141 --> 00:50:40,183
Excuse me.

615
00:50:40,267 --> 00:50:41,935
-What are you doing?
-Who are you?

616
00:50:42,018 --> 00:50:43,687
Get out of there. It's dangerous.

617
00:50:43,770 --> 00:50:44,938
One second.

618
00:50:46,481 --> 00:50:47,315
What is it?

619
00:50:47,816 --> 00:50:49,359
Something strange in the sky.

620
00:51:17,637 --> 00:51:18,597
Goal!

621
00:51:26,354 --> 00:51:27,772
That's enough!

622
00:51:33,028 --> 00:51:33,862
Stop it.

623
00:51:36,531 --> 00:51:38,658
I said stop it! People are getting hurt!

624
00:51:38,742 --> 00:51:41,828
You may be in a cult,
but you're still meant to be a believer.

625
00:51:41,912 --> 00:51:43,496
You can't openly use violence.

626
00:51:44,497 --> 00:51:45,332
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

627
00:51:45,415 --> 00:51:48,418
Listen to me first, you little shit!

628
00:51:48,501 --> 00:51:52,547
Even if you're industry standard
and we're defective, this is wrong!

629
00:51:53,048 --> 00:51:56,468
How dare you use your superpowers
in such a godawful way!

630
00:51:56,551 --> 00:51:57,385
<i>Can you hear--</i>

631
00:51:57,469 --> 00:51:59,846
Again! There you go,
interrupting me again!

632
00:52:01,264 --> 00:52:04,559
How dare you keep interrupting
when an elder is talking to you!

633
00:52:05,185 --> 00:52:06,978
Where did you learn such bad manners?

634
00:52:07,062 --> 00:52:08,480
<i>-Can you--</i>
-I said stop!

635
00:52:08,563 --> 00:52:09,814
Just stop it!

636
00:52:10,815 --> 00:52:13,526
What did those people ever do to you
to deserve this?

637
00:52:14,027 --> 00:52:16,238
Sure, let's say
Trainwreck and Sap deserve it.

638
00:52:16,321 --> 00:52:18,448
What about me and Moon Mi-hui? And Cheong?

639
00:52:18,531 --> 00:52:20,992
And all those other miscellaneous people.

640
00:52:21,076 --> 00:52:24,037
What did they ever do to you
to deserve this? Why?

641
00:52:24,621 --> 00:52:25,705
What's the reason?

642
00:52:29,459 --> 00:52:32,712
People didn't care about
the pain we endured.

643
00:52:33,421 --> 00:52:34,297
No interest at all.

644
00:52:35,257 --> 00:52:37,008
So I don't care either,

645
00:52:37,592 --> 00:52:39,010
whether or not they die.

646
00:52:41,388 --> 00:52:43,181
Never been scolded by an elder, right?

647
00:52:44,599 --> 00:52:47,978
Well, you picked the wrong person
to mess with today.

648
00:52:48,061 --> 00:52:51,314
I'm going to finally drill some manners
into you today--

649
00:52:56,194 --> 00:52:57,153
You little…

650
00:53:15,672 --> 00:53:16,631
Ju-ran.

651
00:53:36,067 --> 00:53:37,068
What happened?

652
00:53:37,569 --> 00:53:38,403
Are you okay?

653
00:53:59,674 --> 00:54:01,593
Ju-ran, are you okay?

654
00:54:06,222 --> 00:54:08,391
Why did you push yourself like this?

655
00:54:08,892 --> 00:54:10,935
<i>You </i>told <i>us</i>
not to use our powers recklessly.

656
00:54:12,312 --> 00:54:13,980
Pal-ho is dead.

657
00:54:17,067 --> 00:54:18,943
And so is Father.

658
00:54:31,748 --> 00:54:33,625
Let's stop this now.

659
00:54:36,086 --> 00:54:38,963
I don't want to lose you too, okay?

660
00:54:40,340 --> 00:54:42,175
I can't forgive them.

661
00:54:42,759 --> 00:54:44,594
I'll kill them all.

662
00:54:47,430 --> 00:54:48,556
You still have me.

663
00:54:50,183 --> 00:54:53,395
We have no one left, Ho-ran.

664
00:54:54,687 --> 00:54:56,022
Avenge us.

665
00:54:57,148 --> 00:54:58,483
All of them.

666
00:54:59,359 --> 00:55:01,027
Destroy them all.

667
00:55:04,906 --> 00:55:07,033
Please do that for me, Ho-ran.

668
00:55:30,432 --> 00:55:31,516
Here they come.

669
00:55:32,851 --> 00:55:34,060
Hey, are you okay?

670
00:55:34,144 --> 00:55:35,145
No.

671
00:55:35,228 --> 00:55:37,230
-My head hurts.
-Earlier, you were all…

672
00:55:37,313 --> 00:55:39,732
They've snapped out of it.

673
00:55:40,900 --> 00:55:42,193
Is it over or what?

674
00:56:07,635 --> 00:56:08,803
Are you hurt badly?

675
00:56:10,889 --> 00:56:12,307
I'm just a bit tired.

676
00:56:21,733 --> 00:56:23,943
What happened with the fireworks?

677
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:28,740
You won't be able to stop it.

678
00:56:30,867 --> 00:56:31,701
Ms. Eun Chae-ni?

679
00:56:40,210 --> 00:56:42,086
It'll be so very pretty.

680
00:56:43,755 --> 00:56:45,215
The truth is,

681
00:56:46,216 --> 00:56:48,510
I've never seen fireworks
in person either.

682
00:57:00,230 --> 00:57:01,814
My final goodbye.

683
00:57:09,364 --> 00:57:14,911
<i>All right,</i>
<i>there really isn't much left of 1999.</i>

684
00:57:14,994 --> 00:57:20,542
<i>Are you all spending the last moments</i>
<i>of the 20th century with your loved ones?</i>

685
00:57:21,042 --> 00:57:27,006
<i>There are about five minutes left</i>
<i>until the new millennium begins.</i>

686
00:57:27,090 --> 00:57:32,011
<i>I'm hoping you're all spending</i>
<i>these last few minutes of 1999</i>

687
00:57:32,095 --> 00:57:35,557
<i>with the people you cherish most.</i>

688
00:57:36,099 --> 00:57:39,519
<i>This is the last song I'm playing for you</i>
<i>in the 20th century.</i>

689
00:58:08,548 --> 00:58:11,634
This is the price
of our shepherd Kim Pal-ho's blood.

690
00:58:27,400 --> 00:58:28,776
Chae-ni!

691
00:58:28,860 --> 00:58:30,278
Why, is something wrong?

692
00:58:33,072 --> 00:58:34,365
Why? What is it?

693
00:58:36,951 --> 00:58:38,870
Are you really Eun Chae-ni?

694
00:58:38,953 --> 00:58:40,538
Of course I'm Eun Chae-ni.

695
00:58:40,622 --> 00:58:42,790
Who else would I be, Geum Chae-ni?
What is it?

696
00:58:44,584 --> 00:58:45,585
There…

697
00:58:49,964 --> 00:58:51,966
There's another Chae-ni!

698
00:58:53,551 --> 00:58:54,844
Why am I over there?

699
00:58:57,055 --> 00:58:58,723
Did I just get stabbed?

700
00:58:59,223 --> 00:59:00,058
No!

701
00:59:06,022 --> 00:59:06,981
What's this?

702
00:59:24,374 --> 00:59:27,752
Breathe. I need you to stay awake.
I'll call an ambulance.

703
00:59:28,336 --> 00:59:29,253
Are you…

704
00:59:31,506 --> 00:59:33,257
worrying about me?

705
00:59:35,843 --> 00:59:36,678
Yeah.

706
00:59:42,183 --> 00:59:43,726
-Look at that!
-Wow.

707
00:59:43,810 --> 00:59:44,811
<i>Just like you did</i>

708
00:59:45,478 --> 00:59:46,729
<i>for me back then.</i>

709
00:59:46,813 --> 00:59:48,564
Wow, look at that fish!

710
00:59:48,648 --> 00:59:50,483
<i>You didn't just comfort me,</i>

711
00:59:51,234 --> 00:59:53,486
<i>you comforted all the kids in there.</i>

712
00:59:53,569 --> 00:59:54,779
There are so many!

713
00:59:57,990 --> 00:59:59,075
It…

714
01:00:02,370 --> 01:00:03,996
would have been nice…

715
01:00:06,833 --> 01:00:08,167
if you'd been on my side.

716
01:00:23,015 --> 01:00:23,933
No.

717
01:00:24,976 --> 01:00:25,935
No.

718
01:00:26,853 --> 01:00:27,979
Ho-ran.

719
01:00:29,397 --> 01:00:30,898
No!

720
01:00:33,943 --> 01:00:36,446
Is she dead? Is she really?

721
01:00:36,529 --> 01:00:39,615
Her pulse is still there.
Can you call an ambulance?

722
01:00:40,533 --> 01:00:43,578
Damn it, I think I dropped
my cell phone somewhere. Hold on.

723
01:00:44,829 --> 01:00:47,415
Ro-bin, let's move her inside first.

724
01:00:48,541 --> 01:00:50,168
Where could I have dropped…

725
01:00:53,212 --> 01:00:54,589
Honey, where are you going?

726
01:00:55,631 --> 01:00:56,466
Honey!

727
01:00:56,549 --> 01:00:59,218
I told you not to come out
until I told you to.

728
01:00:59,302 --> 01:01:01,137
Honey, where are you going?

729
01:01:19,947 --> 01:01:20,948
What is that?

730
01:01:36,339 --> 01:01:43,346
THE JUDGE IS STANDING AT THE DOOR
JAMES 5:9

731
01:02:15,127 --> 01:02:17,004
You won't be able to stop it.

732
01:02:21,467 --> 01:02:25,054
The prophecy will be fulfilled as planned.

733
01:02:26,472 --> 01:02:28,474
You will know when the apocalypse comes.

734
01:02:29,517 --> 01:02:31,269
Those who do not believe

735
01:02:31,769 --> 01:02:34,981
will be cast into the hellfire
known as death.

736
01:02:36,190 --> 01:02:38,359
As for those who are saved,

737
01:02:38,860 --> 01:02:43,030
they will gain eternal life
as Wunderkinder!

738
01:02:57,336 --> 01:02:59,672
So that was the real bomb.

739
01:03:02,133 --> 01:03:03,759
It wasn't the fireworks?

740
01:03:37,043 --> 01:03:40,087
Maybe it was never
something we could stop.

741
01:04:19,585 --> 01:04:22,296
I said I wanted to live
to see the apocalypse.

742
01:04:23,005 --> 01:04:25,091
I guess my wish came true.

743
01:04:28,844 --> 01:04:30,471
But what a shame.

744
01:04:33,307 --> 01:04:35,393
I no longer want to see

745
01:04:36,102 --> 01:04:37,687
this goddamn apocalypse.

746
01:04:39,647 --> 01:04:42,233
Chae-ni, what are you saying?
You're making me nervous.

747
01:04:43,150 --> 01:04:47,154
Ro-bin, toss me and Mr. Son up there.

748
01:04:48,406 --> 01:04:49,657
Why me?

749
01:04:49,740 --> 01:04:51,867
There's nowhere to hold on to.

750
01:04:51,951 --> 01:04:54,704
Just stick me on securely,
then you can fall off.

751
01:04:54,787 --> 01:04:57,123
I'll try to teleport with that airship.

752
01:04:57,999 --> 01:05:00,459
And what if something terrible
happens to you?

753
01:05:00,543 --> 01:05:03,087
Don't worry.
You know that I don't die, even if I do.

754
01:05:03,170 --> 01:05:07,341
Why would you not die? Don't you know
how that heart ended up with you?

755
01:05:08,718 --> 01:05:11,721
If anything goes wrong, that heart
could be all that's left of you.

756
01:05:11,804 --> 01:05:13,597
That's a bomb, you doofus.

757
01:05:13,681 --> 01:05:15,891
If it explodes,
you'd be blown to smithereens.

758
01:05:15,975 --> 01:05:17,518
What would we say to Grandma?

759
01:05:17,601 --> 01:05:21,522
It'd be a secret, of course.
Don't tell her, Kang Ro-bin, okay?

760
01:05:21,605 --> 01:05:23,232
I'll be back soon.

761
01:05:23,315 --> 01:05:24,150
No.

762
01:05:24,817 --> 01:05:27,278
Then let's go together.
I'll go up there with you.

763
01:05:28,946 --> 01:05:29,780
In your state?

764
01:05:31,323 --> 01:05:33,367
You'll just be a burden, okay?

765
01:05:33,451 --> 01:05:36,537
Just make sure to catch us when we fall.

766
01:05:36,620 --> 01:05:39,165
Catch Mr. Son first. Then me.

767
01:05:39,248 --> 01:05:40,541
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

768
01:05:42,043 --> 01:05:45,171
You know I could die
if I fall from that height, don't you?

769
01:05:46,005 --> 01:05:48,299
So I'm asking you to catch me.

770
01:05:48,382 --> 01:05:52,094
It would be a darn shame
to die after completing the mission, no?

771
01:05:56,057 --> 01:05:57,808
Hurry up. We don't have much time.

772
01:05:59,935 --> 01:06:01,187
It'll be okay.

773
01:06:12,573 --> 01:06:13,407
Okay.

774
01:06:18,245 --> 01:06:19,288
Let's do it.

775
01:06:20,706 --> 01:06:21,582
Why the hell not?

776
01:06:27,213 --> 01:06:28,339
You look pretty today.

777
01:06:30,591 --> 01:06:31,884
It's done.

778
01:06:35,137 --> 01:06:36,180
You know what, Ro-bin?

779
01:06:37,306 --> 01:06:39,141
You're fugly when you smile.

780
01:06:41,560 --> 01:06:43,479
Eun Chae-ni, I swear, you…

781
01:06:43,562 --> 01:06:45,272
Just toss us already, King Sap!

782
01:06:45,356 --> 01:06:46,565
You Sappy Sap!

783
01:06:53,697 --> 01:06:55,866
King Sap!

784
01:07:18,722 --> 01:07:19,640
I

785
01:07:20,933 --> 01:07:22,268
want Eun Chae-ni

786
01:07:22,977 --> 01:07:24,895
to just

787
01:07:25,479 --> 01:07:26,480
disappear

788
01:07:26,564 --> 01:07:28,858
forever!

789
01:07:29,358 --> 01:07:30,401
-Go!
-What?

790
01:07:30,484 --> 01:07:31,902
You need to climb up.

791
01:07:31,986 --> 01:07:33,529
Come on. Go a little further!

792
01:07:33,612 --> 01:07:34,655
You go!

793
01:07:36,532 --> 01:07:37,908
Wait, one second.

794
01:07:37,992 --> 01:07:39,034
Just a bit more.

795
01:07:39,118 --> 01:07:40,161
Don't fall off yet.

796
01:07:40,244 --> 01:07:41,287
-Go!
-Stay stuck.

797
01:07:41,370 --> 01:07:42,329
Go!

798
01:07:42,413 --> 01:07:44,832
-Go!
-Wait a minute, Mr. Son.

799
01:07:45,332 --> 01:07:46,458
Ow, easy!

800
01:07:56,302 --> 01:07:57,469
I'm up.

801
01:07:58,053 --> 01:08:01,140
Mr. Son, you should go now!

802
01:08:01,223 --> 01:08:04,518
You were really impressive today.

803
01:08:05,352 --> 01:08:06,270
Hey.

804
01:08:07,605 --> 01:08:08,731
Do good, you punk!

805
01:08:16,655 --> 01:08:17,990
Still,

806
01:08:18,657 --> 01:08:22,745
I hope Eun Chae-ni comes back
safe and sound!

807
01:09:18,884 --> 01:09:22,346
<i>All right,</i>
<i>we really don't have much time left now.</i>

808
01:09:22,429 --> 01:09:25,349
<i>Let's start the countdown.</i>

809
01:09:26,934 --> 01:09:27,768
<i>Ten,</i>

810
01:09:28,435 --> 01:09:29,270
<i>nine,</i>

811
01:09:30,354 --> 01:09:31,230
<i>eight,</i>

812
01:09:32,022 --> 01:09:32,856
<i>seven,</i>

813
01:09:33,524 --> 01:09:34,358
<i>six,</i>

814
01:09:35,192 --> 01:09:36,110
<i>five,</i>

815
01:09:36,694 --> 01:09:37,653
<i>four,</i>

816
01:09:38,153 --> 01:09:39,154
<i>three,</i>

817
01:09:39,863 --> 01:09:40,948
<i>two,</i>

818
01:09:41,031 --> 01:09:42,032
<i>one!</i>

819
01:10:13,731 --> 01:10:14,565
Eunie.

820
01:10:25,784 --> 01:10:27,578
<i>The year 2000!</i>

821
01:10:27,661 --> 01:10:31,081
<i>The new millennium has finally begun.</i>

822
01:10:40,007 --> 01:10:40,924
No.

823
01:10:43,177 --> 01:10:44,094
No!

824
01:10:45,220 --> 01:10:47,389
No!

825
01:11:06,408 --> 01:11:07,326
Where am I?

826
01:11:07,409 --> 01:11:08,827
-What is that?
-In the sky!

827
01:11:10,579 --> 01:11:12,206
What happened?

828
01:11:26,512 --> 01:11:29,431
I should be watching this with Cheong.

829
01:11:34,603 --> 01:11:35,979
What a view!

830
01:11:45,447 --> 01:11:46,865
We stopped it.

831
01:11:47,616 --> 01:11:48,826
We

832
01:11:50,369 --> 01:11:52,496
saved these people.

833
01:11:53,455 --> 01:11:55,332
When Chae-ni comes back,

834
01:11:57,042 --> 01:11:59,002
please make sure you catch her, Master.

835
01:12:00,045 --> 01:12:00,879
Yeah.

836
01:12:12,850 --> 01:12:14,810
She's late. Did she go somewhere far?

837
01:12:15,310 --> 01:12:17,604
Did she go to Canada again?

838
01:12:19,731 --> 01:12:24,278
Even if she went to the North Pole,
not Canada,

839
01:12:24,361 --> 01:12:27,865
she should've been back by now
because she'd be teleporting.

840
01:12:28,449 --> 01:12:29,324
Damn it.

841
01:12:30,284 --> 01:12:31,994
Stop saying dumb stuff.

842
01:13:00,230 --> 01:13:03,942
<i>And so, the year 2000 began</i>
<i>with nothing out of the ordinary.</i>

843
01:13:04,443 --> 01:13:08,113
<i>Finally, the new millennium has begun.</i>

844
01:13:08,697 --> 01:13:13,202
<i>With the start of the year 2000,</i>
<i>we have some news of an incident.</i>

845
01:13:13,702 --> 01:13:17,289
<i>Last night,</i>
<i>a sudden squall occurred in Haeseong.</i>

846
01:13:17,372 --> 01:13:18,832
<i>During its Millennium Festival…</i>

847
01:13:18,916 --> 01:13:22,169
My goodness,
what kind of squall flips over cars?

848
01:13:24,671 --> 01:13:27,132
And it ruined the parade too.

849
01:13:27,716 --> 01:13:30,135
Still, Cheong looks great
in these pictures.

850
01:13:32,471 --> 01:13:34,056
Do you really not remember?

851
01:13:34,556 --> 01:13:38,519
Do you really not remember how cool I was
when I saved you two that day?

852
01:13:38,602 --> 01:13:41,438
I took you to shelter in the record store.

853
01:13:41,522 --> 01:13:44,399
And then I saved people and stuff,
you know?

854
01:13:44,483 --> 01:13:46,652
Now you're resorting to telling
outlandish lies?

855
01:13:49,238 --> 01:13:52,366
Why not just say you flew around
with a cape on?

856
01:13:52,866 --> 01:13:54,660
I'm so sick of you.

857
01:13:59,665 --> 01:14:00,791
-Dad.
-Yeah?

858
01:14:00,874 --> 01:14:02,543
-My lunch box.
-Didn't I give it to you?

859
01:14:02,626 --> 01:14:03,710
There it is.

860
01:14:07,714 --> 01:14:09,633
They are absolutely ridiculous.

861
01:14:09,716 --> 01:14:10,842
Unbelievable…

862
01:14:12,761 --> 01:14:17,057
<i>And no one remembered the events</i>
<i>that took place that day.</i>

863
01:14:17,766 --> 01:14:18,850
<i>A squall?</i>

864
01:14:18,934 --> 01:14:21,186
How could a squall blow a car away?

865
01:14:21,270 --> 01:14:22,354
Tell me about it.

866
01:14:22,437 --> 01:14:23,647
How did you get this?

867
01:14:25,524 --> 01:14:26,358
What the…

868
01:14:27,234 --> 01:14:28,944
Why doesn't anyone remember?

869
01:14:30,445 --> 01:14:31,572
Could it be…

870
01:14:34,825 --> 01:14:35,909
Honey.

871
01:14:36,618 --> 01:14:37,869
Honey!

872
01:14:38,370 --> 01:14:39,246
Honey!

873
01:14:41,081 --> 01:14:42,457
Why are you standing there?

874
01:14:46,795 --> 01:14:49,506
Honey, yes, it's me.

875
01:14:54,219 --> 01:14:57,097
I saved you and Cheong,

876
01:14:57,598 --> 01:14:59,141
and I saved everyone.

877
01:15:00,267 --> 01:15:01,351
What are you on about?

878
01:15:02,811 --> 01:15:06,148
I don't see Cheong. Go and find her.

879
01:15:06,231 --> 01:15:07,733
Cheong!

880
01:15:08,775 --> 01:15:10,152
Son Cheong!

881
01:15:11,278 --> 01:15:13,113
No, I saved you…

882
01:15:14,197 --> 01:15:15,699
We did it!

883
01:15:16,199 --> 01:15:17,909
We saved you and Haeseong

884
01:15:18,827 --> 01:15:20,912
from the apocalypse!

885
01:15:20,996 --> 01:15:22,748
So why don't you remember?

886
01:15:27,628 --> 01:15:29,421
<i>For some unknown reason,</i>

887
01:15:30,255 --> 01:15:33,300
<i>the heroes of that day</i>
<i>disappeared from everyone's memories.</i>

888
01:15:33,383 --> 01:15:34,551
Why?

889
01:15:35,344 --> 01:15:37,763
Why do you all look so clueless?

890
01:15:38,430 --> 01:15:42,392
For God's sake! Do you really think
this car flipped over from a squall?

891
01:15:42,476 --> 01:15:43,602
<i>But</i>

892
01:15:44,436 --> 01:15:45,437
<i>I…</i>

893
01:15:46,188 --> 01:15:47,564
My darling daughter.

894
01:15:48,065 --> 01:15:50,484
Have a good day today too, okay?

895
01:15:51,860 --> 01:15:53,236
You did great, Dad.

896
01:15:53,320 --> 01:15:54,196
Yeah.

897
01:15:56,073 --> 01:15:57,074
What?

898
01:16:01,953 --> 01:16:03,580
Yeah, thanks, Cheong.

899
01:16:10,045 --> 01:16:11,713
Thank you, honey.

900
01:16:19,137 --> 01:16:22,599
HEARTY HOUSE

901
01:16:26,812 --> 01:16:28,480
She'll come back.

902
01:16:29,564 --> 01:16:31,566
My baby will come back, yes.

903
01:16:32,651 --> 01:16:33,819
She just went too far,

904
01:16:34,945 --> 01:16:37,239
so she's taking a while
to find her way back.

905
01:16:38,240 --> 01:16:39,074
Well…

906
01:16:40,951 --> 01:16:42,703
that's possible, isn't it?

907
01:16:43,203 --> 01:16:44,037
Yeah.

908
01:17:37,174 --> 01:17:41,636
FLORALA

909
01:18:00,322 --> 01:18:01,656
Those little shits.

910
01:18:17,005 --> 01:18:18,840
They say you have to make a grave,

911
01:18:18,924 --> 01:18:22,302
even if it's empty,
for someone who died away from home.

912
01:18:24,387 --> 01:18:28,225
So that their soul doesn't wander
the netherworld aimlessly.

913
01:18:53,124 --> 01:18:54,793
MEMORIAL TABLET
EUN CHAE-NI

914
01:19:03,593 --> 01:19:05,011
Enjoy.

915
01:19:07,639 --> 01:19:09,349
Please enjoy.

916
01:19:11,685 --> 01:19:14,521
Not much to eat here.
What kind of party is this?

917
01:19:15,105 --> 01:19:16,815
You shouldn't eat with your hands.

918
01:19:16,898 --> 01:19:18,650
Then hurry up with the serving.

919
01:19:18,733 --> 01:19:21,194
Sorry, we're just giving out
generous portions.

920
01:19:21,278 --> 01:19:23,989
If you're starved, come here.
I'll serve you first.

921
01:19:29,953 --> 01:19:31,705
Is this for a 49-day ritual?

922
01:19:32,205 --> 01:19:33,290
Did someone die?

923
01:19:33,790 --> 01:19:35,333
Who died?

924
01:19:37,544 --> 01:19:38,503
You…

925
01:19:41,006 --> 01:19:42,048
You…

926
01:19:42,549 --> 01:19:43,383
Eunie.

927
01:19:44,301 --> 01:19:45,635
Is that you, Eunie?

928
01:19:46,636 --> 01:19:47,679
Chae-ni!

929
01:19:48,763 --> 01:19:49,890
You mean Eun Chae-ni?

930
01:19:49,973 --> 01:19:50,932
Goodness!

931
01:19:53,518 --> 01:19:54,686
Goodness gracious!

932
01:19:55,687 --> 01:19:56,605
Good heavens!

933
01:19:57,105 --> 01:19:59,024
My goodness, Chae-ni.

934
01:20:04,446 --> 01:20:06,990
Let me look at you. My goodness.

935
01:20:07,073 --> 01:20:09,826
It took me a while to get back, didn't it?

936
01:20:10,327 --> 01:20:13,538
I tried to go
to the furthest place I knew,

937
01:20:13,622 --> 01:20:16,249
and I ended up in a desert
on the other side of the planet.

938
01:20:16,333 --> 01:20:18,460
And I guess it was too far away

939
01:20:18,543 --> 01:20:20,545
because I couldn't make my way back.

940
01:20:20,629 --> 01:20:22,172
I had no passport, no money.

941
01:20:22,255 --> 01:20:26,426
So the journey back here
was absolutely grueling.

942
01:20:26,968 --> 01:20:29,512
But who died? Everyone's here.

943
01:20:29,596 --> 01:20:32,223
-My baby isn't dead.
-Who?

944
01:20:33,266 --> 01:20:34,893
My baby isn't dead, is she?

945
01:20:35,393 --> 01:20:37,520
My baby's alive!

946
01:20:43,109 --> 01:20:44,611
Wait.

947
01:20:44,694 --> 01:20:47,405
Wait, I'm starving, okay?
Give me some food first.

948
01:20:47,489 --> 01:20:48,823
-Food.
-Right, food.

949
01:20:49,491 --> 01:20:50,825
You brat!

950
01:20:51,409 --> 01:20:53,536
How can you be so unfazed?

951
01:20:53,620 --> 01:20:55,705
Do you know how sad we were?

952
01:20:55,789 --> 01:20:59,376
I knew better than anyone
that I wasn't dead,

953
01:20:59,459 --> 01:21:00,961
so why would I be sad?

954
01:21:01,586 --> 01:21:02,587
Is that so?

955
01:21:02,671 --> 01:21:04,255
I guess you're right!

956
01:21:07,175 --> 01:21:09,219
Can we get a wet towel here?

957
01:21:10,387 --> 01:21:11,846
You stinky little shit.

958
01:21:12,847 --> 01:21:14,975
I do stink, don't I? Have you been good?

959
01:21:18,061 --> 01:21:19,312
Food.

960
01:21:20,146 --> 01:21:21,523
Oh, my baby.

961
01:21:22,023 --> 01:21:23,400
The rice cakes are good today.

962
01:22:02,522 --> 01:22:04,274
Aren't you happy to see me, Master?

963
01:22:06,860 --> 01:22:08,028
What took you so long?

964
01:22:10,905 --> 01:22:13,992
It took me a while
to get used to being a stowaway.

965
01:22:14,868 --> 01:22:17,370
Why? Did you miss me?

966
01:22:20,331 --> 01:22:23,835
It was a refreshing change,
not having someone cling to me.

967
01:22:28,882 --> 01:22:29,758
Stay back, you.

968
01:22:33,428 --> 01:22:36,181
You try not washing for three weeks.
I bet you'd smell worse!

969
01:22:37,140 --> 01:22:39,309
Let's meet again after you've washed up.

970
01:22:47,108 --> 01:22:49,486
You won't be able to wash this off
with a shower.

971
01:22:49,986 --> 01:22:52,363
It'll last a whole week.

972
01:22:57,327 --> 01:22:58,411
You're…

973
01:23:00,163 --> 01:23:01,831
such a pain, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

974
01:23:04,292 --> 01:23:05,210
I like you.

975
01:24:12,318 --> 01:24:14,028
<i>Some people are different.</i>

976
01:24:16,406 --> 01:24:18,741
<i>Others are late bloomers.</i>

977
01:24:20,451 --> 01:24:21,536
<i>Others</i>

978
01:24:22,328 --> 01:24:25,123
<i>prefer the quiet outskirts.</i>

979
01:24:25,874 --> 01:24:27,542
HAESEONG CITY HALL

980
01:24:27,625 --> 01:24:29,085
<i>But</i>

981
01:24:29,919 --> 01:24:32,046
<i>there's no such thing</i>

982
01:24:32,964 --> 01:24:34,299
<i>as a nobody.</i>

983
01:25:43,409 --> 01:25:45,912
-Yes?
-Is it done yet?

984
01:25:46,412 --> 01:25:48,331
No, just a moment.

985
01:25:49,123 --> 01:25:51,000
Just bring me what you have so far.

986
01:25:51,084 --> 01:25:51,918
Okay.

987
01:25:54,128 --> 01:25:56,422
Oh, for crying out loud.

988
01:25:56,506 --> 01:25:58,383
I told you to go back to Seoul!

989
01:25:58,466 --> 01:26:00,927
I don't know why you're still here,
driving me nuts.

990
01:26:01,010 --> 01:26:02,804
Next time, I'll do it all.

991
01:26:03,429 --> 01:26:05,139
Here, get this done quickly.

992
01:26:06,057 --> 01:26:08,184
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

993
01:26:08,268 --> 01:26:11,229
Yes, the entrance has been blocked off.

994
01:26:11,813 --> 01:26:14,357
-Anything left?
-It's all charred.

995
01:26:18,695 --> 01:26:19,779
Search every inch.

996
01:26:19,862 --> 01:26:22,031
And report to me if you find anything.

997
01:26:22,115 --> 01:26:22,949
Yes, sir.

998
01:30:05,880 --> 01:30:10,885
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

